title.narrative: Somaliland Development Fund Capital Programme Costs (CDEL)

description.narrative: This activity (Somaliland Development Fund Capital Programme Costs (CDEL)) is a component of Somaliland Development Fund aligned to the priorities of National Development Plan reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £15,374,077. This component benefits Somalia, and works in the following sector(s): Education facilities and training, Water supply - large systems, Social Protection, Road transport, Communications policy and administrative management, Livestock, Fishery development, Bio-diversity. , with the following implementing partners: AECOM, Crown Agents Bank, Crown Agents Limited. The start date is 12-08-2013 and the end date is 31-08-2018.
